rder=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=95%><tr><td bgcolor=#CCCCCC><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#8B0000 class=headings><font color=#000000>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#8B0000 class=headings><font color=#000000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cuinar>Cuinar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/03 10:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Taunt - Mezzed Mobs - Seems to not fit the current theories</span><hr size=1> Lots of recent taunt posts.  I was about to buy into the single taunt and then hold taunt available to use again when you loose aggro, but I have a concern.<br>
<br>
When dealing with a number of mezzed mobs, such as in Hate, a single taunt will not transfer the aggro to the MA, if the mob has been mezzed for any length of time.  The longer the mob has been mezzed, the more taunt keystrokes are needed to prevent ping-pong effects once the mob is broken.<br>
<br>
A mob that has been mezzed for a long-time may need 3 or 4 taunts to eliminate the ping-pong before you wake up the mob.  Recently, mezzed mobs may need zero taunting.  Conclusion: Seems like the repeated taunting builds aggro before the mez break.<br>
<br>
As I know this is how critters respond to mezzing, how can the single keystroke theory to max taunt be correct?  Am I missing something?   <br>
<br>
Really would like Faate's read on this. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cuinar>Cuinar</A> at: 3/28/03 10:43:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=strikingone>StrikingOne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/03 10:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunt - Mezzed Mobs - Seems to not fit the current theor</span><hr size=1> Well, if it actually matters, IE a mob that hits for 500 + its always good to /assist mob to see where the agro is.<br>
<br>
Mobs that have been mezed over and over will of course have more hate than a single mez. Sometimes taunt is failed, or sometimes you need to taunt a couple times to build up that much hate. <br>
<br>
Taunt has a set amount of agro it will push you up ( my own personal opinion is about 500 hate), it is not like Area taunt, that will put you at the top regardless of the fact that you start at 0 hate and the current top spot is sitting at 10k hate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmlokk>Grimmlokk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1101<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/03 1:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunt - Mezzed Mobs - Seems to not fit the current theor</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>A mob that has been mezzed for a long-time may need 3 or 4 taunts to eliminate the ping-pong before you wake up the mob.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
 Not sure you grasp the &quot;current theory&quot;. Any mob might take 3-4 taunts to get agro. It's the nature of taunt, it's not successful every time. And the close the mob is to your level(or higher) the less likely you are to have a succesful taunt.<br>
<br>
 Since you specified Hate specifically, last time I was there which was admittedly a long time ago, taunt worked like everywhere else.<br>
<br>
 *Any* successful taunt puts you on top of the hate list. Either matching the top person, or puts you 1 point above. Not positive. The only reason a mob should ping-pong when you break mez if you had a successful taunt is sitting people. Or low HP agro. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=372117"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spingrim3c.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eldryc>Eldryc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/03 1:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunt - Mezzed Mobs - Seems to not fit the current theor</span><hr size=1> I think the further down the aggro list you are, the lower your percentage chance of a successful taunt is.  If that's the case, then yes, a mob that's been mezzed repeatedly will most likely, but not definitely, take more than one taunt before one of them works, vaulting you to the top o the list.  That's perfectly consistent with the taunt moving you to the top theory.<br>
<br>
&quot;Taunt has a set amount of agro it will<br>
                            push you up ( my own personal opinion<br>
                            is about 500 hate), it is not like Area<br>
                            taunt, that will put you at the top<br>
                            regardless of the fact that you start at<br>
