<br>
ok, this has been argued here about a million times in the past and proven quite convincingly to be untrue.  If all taunt did is add a set amount, then it wouldn't explain how sometimes you can walk up to a mob that someone else has smashed for thousands of dmg and immediately taunt it off of them.   Your chance of a successful taunt in that situation seems to be low, but it does happen.  I've noted it a number of times myself.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pilerboy>pilerboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/03 1:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunt - Mezzed Mobs - Seems to not fit the current theor</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>or sometimes you need to taunt a couple times to build up that much hate.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
